OL,3,C'Addicted': The teenagers who gave up
OL,4,Ctheir phones for a fortnight
OL,6,FAlthough parents can manage settings
OL,7,Fon some devices to help protect their
OL,8,Fchildren's well-being, there are
OL,9,Fgrowing calls for governments to
OL,10,Fintroduce laws to restrict the amount
OL,11,Fof harmful content that is often
OL,12,Freadily available for children and
OL,13,Fyoung people to access online.
OL,15,FThe UK's Online Safety Act will come
OL,16,Finto force in July, but Jersey
OL,17,Fcurrently has no similar legislation
OL,18,Fafter opting to build its own laws
OL,19,Findependently.
